{
  "texts": [
    "Both the hadronic resonance gas model and hadronic transport model UrQMD [76,77] calculations reproduce this trend.",
    "As a function of collision energy, a rise and then fall of the netproton C 4 ∕C 2 (or 2) is expected to indicate the critical behavior near the critical point in the QCD phase diagram.",
    "While results of C 4 ∕C 2 ratios from BES-I have shown dip like energy dependence around 20 GeV, the statistics at lower collision energies are too poor to draw any conclusions regarding this prediction.",
    "Note that at low energies, or equivalently, in the high baryon density region, both the HADES ( √ s NN = 2.4 GeV) and STAR ( √ s NN = 3.0 GeV [159, 160]) high moment proton results are below the Poisson baseline, and the non-critical hadronic transport model calculations reproduce the data at the high baryon density region.",
    "This implies that this energy regime is dominated by hadronic interactions."
  ]
}